Emurua Dikirr MP Johanna Ngeno has accused the government of witch-hunt after he refused to join Jubilee Party.&quot;Frequent disruption of my functions by Jubilee supporters is testimony of the witch-hunt.They are trying to intimidate me so I can support them but that is not going to happen because it is my constitutional right to join a party of my choice,&quot; said Ngeno who spoke at Dikirr Primary School.&nbsp;Ngeno wants police to investigation and take action against a group of youths he claims has been disrupting his meetings.